```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Data Breach Simulation</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        input[type="text"], input[type="password"] {
            width: calc(100% - 22px);
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        button {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Data Breach Simulation</h1>

<form action="#" method="post">
    <label for="ssn">Enter Your Social Security Number:</label>
    <input type="text" id="ssn" name="ssn" placeholder="####-##-####" pattern="\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}" required>

    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

</body>
</html>
```

This HTML form includes:
- A title for the page.
- Labels and input fields for the user to enter their social security number.
- A submit button to process the form.
- Basic styling to make the form visually appealing and user-friendly.

Feel free to customize the form further based on your needs!

